title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 29-2 .44 Magnum 4-Inch Bbl...Near New...Mfd 1980.
postcontent: Here's a very nice Smith & Wesson Model 29-2 double-action .44 Magnum. This revolver is built on the big square butt N-frame, wears the desirable 4" pinned barrel and has the counter-bored ("recessed") chambers. It features the white-outline adjustable rear sight, red ramp front sight, target hammer, target trigger, and smooth target stocks. This handsome revolver is factory finished in bright blue with color case hardened hammer and trigger. Condition is excellent with nearly all of the original finish remaining. There is a light cylinder turn line and a couple of very small handling marks. There is no rust or any pitting. The stocks are in fine shape but do show a little more handling wear than the revolver. The mechanics are in perfect working order with good timing and solid lock-up. The bore is excellent too with bright, sharp rifling. It's quite evident that this was a "safe queen" and saw only limited and careful use since new. According to the serial number, this beauty was manufactured in about 1980-82. A very nice revolver...they just don't make like this any longer!Buyer pays $20.00 shipping.
